<item>
            <title>[CXF-2243] JMSFactory.createJmsListener does not use property from JMSConfiguration to set the receiveTimeout on the constructed Spring DMLC</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-2243</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;JMSFactory.createJmsListener does not use the property value from the JMSConfiguration to set the receiveTimeout on the constructed Spring DMLC. As a result, the constructed DMLC always has the default receiveTimeout value of 1000 milliseconds (which can be quite inefficient). &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12426619">CXF-2243</key>
            <summary>JMSFactory.createJmsListener does not use property from JMSConfiguration to set the receiveTimeout on the constructed Spring DMLC</summary>
