                            <comment id="12715062" author="rgavlin" created="Mon, 1 Jun 2009 11:12:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch allows the JMSConfiguration.receiveTimeout to be used to configure both the conduit/JMSTemplate and the destination/JMSListener. Currently, only the conduit/JMSTemplate is possible.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12715415" author="njiang" created="Tue, 2 Jun 2009 08:22:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Applied patch with thanks to Ron.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;BTW, &lt;br/&gt;
I did a quick fix&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;for working with the spring 2.0.x by setting the template with default timeout value 0 if the JMSConfigurer hasn&apos;t that value.&lt;/p&gt;

